        I_THINK_I_KNOW_WHAT_MAY_BE_TROUBLING                                 = 10653,  -- I think I know what may be troubling you. You remember my pupil Ranemaud, do you not? Talk with him, and he may be able to help you with your predicament.
        THIS_IS_ALL_I_WILL_TELL_YOU_AFTER                                    = 10654,  -- This is all I will tell you. After you have obtained %, bring them and your % to me. I will be waiting.
        WELL_IF_IT_ISN_T_MY_FAVORITE_ADVENTURER                              = 10655,  -- Well, if it isn't my favorite adventurer. How is your training coming along? I can see that you have become quite the samurai.
        BUT_SMALL_TALK_IS_NOT_WHY_YOU_HAVE                                   = 10656,  -- But small talk is not why you have come to me, is it? It is a shame that your % has met such a regrettable fate.
        HOWEVER_YOU_NEED_NOT_WORRY_THE_ONE_PLACE                             = 10657,  -- However, you need not worry. The one place where you can obtain % is here in Norg.
        LIKE_A_SALMON_RETURNS_TO_ITS_BIRTHPLACE_TO                           = 10658,  -- Like a salmon returns to its birthplace to die, all % that are disposed of by their owners make their way back here to Norg. The blade you disposed of is not an exception.
        I_DO_NOT_KNOW_WHAT_REASONS_YOU_HAD                                   = 10659,  -- I do not know what reasons you had when disposing of your %, but the moment that blade left your possession, it became ours once again.
        I_CAN_RETURN_IT_TO_YOU_IF_YOU                                        = 10660,  -- I can return it to you if you wish, but it will cost you. Pay me # gil, and I will give back to you what you once let slip through your hands.
        THE_DESTINY_THAT_LIES_AHEAD_OF_THAT_IS                               = 10661,  -- The destiny that lies ahead of that % is much more important than you could ever imagine. Take care of it this time.
        IT_LOOKS_LIKE_YOU_ARE_STILL_A_LITTLE                                 = 10662,  -- It looks like you are still a little short on gil.
        AH_YOU_RE_BACK_AND_JUST_IN_TIME                                      = 10663,  -- Ah, you're back! And just in time, I might say. The date of the ritual is approaching fast.
        FOR_THIS_NEXT_ASSIGNMENT_GILGAMESH_SPECIFICALLY_REQUESTED_THE        = 10664,  -- For this next assignment, Gilgamesh specifically requested the assistance of the previous owner of the %.
        THAT_IS_UNFORTUNATE_BUT_THERE_STILL_IS_TIME                          = 10665,  -- That is unfortunate, but there still is time. Please reconsider your decision.
        EXCELLENT_NOW_LET_ME_SHOW_YOU_INTO_GILGAMESH                         = 10666,  -- Excellent. Now let me show you into Gilgamesh's quarters.
        ARRRG_IF_IT_ISN_T_ME_MATEY_WE                                        = 10667,  -- Arrrg, if it isn't me matey, %. We be mighty grateful fer yer help 'n this one.
        I_M_SURE_JAUC_S_ALREADY_TOLD_YA                                      = 10668,  -- I'm sure Jauc's already told ya 'bout the upcomin' ritual we be holdin'. We call it Yomi Okuri. In Far Eastern legend, Yomi is the name of the place where the spirits of the dead roam.
        LET_ME_EXPLAIN                                                       = 10669,  -- Let me explain...
        TWENTY_YEARS_AGO_BEFORE_THE_FALL_OF_CASTLE                           = 10670,  -- Twenty years ago, before the fall of Castle Zvahl and the Shadow Lord, a small country was wiped off the face of Vana'diel by those bloodthirsty beastmen.
        THAT_COUNTRY_WAS_KNOWN_AS_THE_MARQUISATE_OF                          = 10671,  -- That country was known as the Marquisate of Tavnazia. The flag we raise here in Norg be the flag of that lost nation.
        IT_WAS_A_GRUESOME_BATTLE_CITIZENS_OF_TAVNAZIA                        = 10672,  -- It was a gruesome battle. Citizens of Tavnazia, soldiers from the three nations... Nearly all were slaughtered in a matter of hours.
        I_TOO_SAW_THE_APOCALYPSE_THAT_HAPPENED_THE                           = 10673,  -- I, too, saw the apocalypse that happened the day Tavnazia fell. When 'twas all over, the handful of us that remained escaped on a tiny ship.
        BUT_MOST_OF_ME_MATEYS_WERE_ALREADY_IN                                = 10674,  -- But most of me mateys were already in bad shape and didn't survive the long journey home. Only a few of us made it back to Valkurm alive.
        WHEN_WE_ARRIVED_AT_THE_DUNES_WE_FOUND                                = 10675,  -- When we arrived at the dunes, we found that there were others that had tried escapin', but failed...the wreckage of their ships scattered 'bout the beaches.
        THOSE_WHO_COULD_STILL_MOVE_USED_WHAT_REMAINED                        = 10676,  -- Those who could still move used what remained of their energy to dig simple graves for those that had passed. But this would not be enough to appease the troubled souls that lingered in those sands.
        WITHOUT_A_GUIDIN_HAND_THE_SOULS_REMAIN_IN                            = 10677,  -- Without a guidin' hand, the souls remain in this world, gettin' angrier an' angrier. The Yomi Okuri ritual is held to show these lost spirits the way t'their proper place of restin'.
        JAUC_YOU_TAKE_IT_FROM_HERE                                           = 10678,  -- Jauc, you take it from here.
        YES_SIR                                                              = 10679,  -- Yes, sir.
        FOR_THE_YOMI_OKURI_TO_BE_PROPERLY_CARRIED                            = 10680,  -- For the Yomi Okuri to be properly carried out, a sacred katana must be made. Your % has already been used to forge the blade of the katana. However, we are still one step away from completion.
        SOMEWHERE_ON_THE_MAINLANDS_IS_A_PLACE_CALLED                         = 10681,  -- Somewhere on the mainlands is a place called the Labyrinth of Onzozo. In those caves lurks a mammoth bird. To complete the sacred katana, I require % from that beast.
        HOWEVER_THIS_BIRD_RARELY_EVER_SETS_FORTH_FROM                        = 10682,  -- However, this bird rarely ever sets forth from its nest. It must be lured out with a special kind of bait.
        AN_THE_ONLY_ONE_OF_ME_MATES_THAT                                     = 10683,  -- An' the only one of me mates that can brew a bait fine enough to make that pecker show its beak would be our head cook, Washu. Get some from her before ya leave.
        OH_AN_WATCH_YER_BACK_IN_THOSE_CAVES                                  = 10684,  -- Oh, an' watch yer back in those caves. They be crawlin' with all sorts of terrible beasts. Get it, grab the %, and be outta there quick, if ya know what's good fer ya.
        DO_NOT_FORGET_TO_OBTAIN_SOME_OF_WASHU                                = 10685,  -- Do not forget to obtain some of Washu's tasty wurst before you set off for the Labyrinth of Onzozo. You will need it to lure the giant bird out of its lair.
        YES_THIS_IS_EXACTLY_WHAT_I_NEED_TO                                   = 10686,  -- Yes, this % is exactly what I need to complete the sacred katana. Now all I require is time...
        DO_NOT_RUSH_ME_THIS_JOB_REQUIRES_EXTREME                             = 10687,  -- Do not rush me! This job requires extreme concentration. Think of the consequences if I were to hurry through my work!
        THAT_IS_THE_NAME_I_BESTOW_UPON_THIS                                  = 10688,  -- %... That is the name I bestow upon this sacred katana. Now, all that remains is for you to take the blade to Valkurm and complete the ritual.
        IT_IS_DURING_THIS_TIME_BEYOND_DUSK_THAT                              = 10689,  -- It is during this time beyond dusk that you must thrust % into the secluded beach that lies on the other side of the far western caves in the Valkurm Dunes. Only then will the spirits be set free.
        FROM_THE_HOUR_IN_WHICH_THE_SANDS_ARE                                 = 10690,  -- From the hour in which the sands are ruled by darkness until they once again are graced by light...
        WELCOME_BACK_THE_NEW_FORM_THAT_BLADE_HAS                             = 10691,  -- Welcome back, %. The new form that blade has taken is the proof that you were successful in your mission. I applaud you on your bravery.
        GILGAMESH_HAS_ASKED_ME_TO_PRESENT_YOU_WITH                           = 10692,  -- Gilgamesh has asked me to present you with this as a token of our appreciation. Wear it with pride and let it guide you on your path in life.
        NORG_HAS_MANY_TIES_WITH_THE_LOST_NATION                              = 10693,  -- Norg has many ties with the lost nation of Tavnazia, and many people here still think of it as their homeland. The battle fought twenty years ago took the lives of many of our brothers, but the sacrifices that they made have not been in vain.
        THAT_DAY_SOMETHING_IN_GILGAMESH_CHANGED_HE_TRANSFORMED               = 10694,  -- That day, something in Gilgamesh changed. He transformed from a simple soldier to a great leader who would bring us together and create the Norg of today.
        SO_YOU_RE_THE_ADVENTURER_THAT_GILGAMESH_SENT                         = 10695,  -- So you're the adventurer that Gilgamesh sent, eh? Get out a piece of paper and a pencil. You're going to have to go fetch me the following four items.
        WHAT_YOU_THOUGHT_I_D_HAVE_EVERYTHING_YOU                             = 10696,  -- What? You thought I'd have everything you need here? With the way these hooligans eat, I barely have enough grub to feed the dogs! Oh, don't worry. The way you adventurers put everything up on auction, you should be able to get your hands on these items easy enough.
        ALL_I_NEED_IS_AND                                                    = 10697,  -- All I need is %, %, %, and %.
        WHEN_YOU_VE_GOT_ALL_FOUR_BRING_THEM                                  = 10698,  -- When you've got all four, bring them to me. I'll whip you up your bait in no time.
        WHAT_DID_YOU_FORGET_WHAT_I_NEED_YOU                                  = 10699,  -- What, did you forget what I need you to bring already? And you call yourself an adventurer!
        WELL_THAT_WAS_QUICK_PRETTY_GOOD_FOR_AN                               = 10700,  -- Well, that was quick. Pretty good for an adventurer. There may be some hope for you yet! Ha ha ha!
        NOW_LET_ME_WHIP_UP_YOUR_BIRD_BAIT                                    = 10701,  -- Now, let me whip up your bird bait, just like I promised.
        HERE_YOU_GO_BE_CAREFUL_THOUGH_FROM_WHAT                              = 10702,  -- Here you go. Be careful, though. From what I hear, that Onzozo place is a lot rougher than our jungles.
        WHY_ARE_YOU_STILL_HERE_YOU_VE_GOT                                    = 10703,  -- Why are you still here? You've got to get my bait to the birdy before it goes bad. If you were a monster, would you settle for a spoiled meal?
        ONCE_AGAIN_TROUBLE_IS_BREWING_IN_NORG_AND                            = 10704,  -- %! Once again, trouble is brewing in Norg, and we require your services.
        I_SEE_SO_YOU_ARE_BUSY_HOWEVER_THERE                                  = 10705,  -- I see. So you are busy... However, there is still time. I pray that you will return to us quickly.
        YOUR_GRATITUDE_IS_APPRECIATED_BY_ALL_OF_US                           = 10706,  -- Your gratitude is appreciated by all of us here in Norg. Now let us proceed to Gilgamesh's chambers.
        ARRRG_WELCOME_BACK_LET_ME_FILL_YA_IN                                 = 10707,  -- Arrrg, welcome back, %. Let me fill ya in on the predicament we've got ourselves into.
        A_THIEF_S_ROBBED_US_OF_ONE_OF                                        = 10708,  -- A thief's robbed us of one of our treasures. Me thinks it be another band o'pirates. I've got me men out on the trail of 'em now.
        YA_MAY_THINK_THAT_PROBLEMS_BETWEEN_PIRATES_SHOULD                    = 10709,  -- Ya may think that problems between pirates should be solved by pirates--and yer right. But this time, the situation's a wee bit more complicated.
        THE_ITEM_THE_THIEF_STOLE_WAS_AN_ANCIENT                              = 10710,  -- The item the thief stole was an ancient helmet left by me ancestors called %. But this ain't no ordinary helmet.
        IT_S_SAID_THAT_ME_FATHER_TRAPPED_THE                                 = 10711,  -- It's said that me father trapped the spirit of an evil demon in that helmet after a grueling battle in the Northlands. He put numerous magical seals on it t'keep the beast at bay.
        THIS_PROBABLY_BE_THE_REASON_THAT_OUR_RIVAL                           = 10712,  -- This probably be the reason that our rival pirates decided t'lay their grimy hands on it.
        T_MAKE_A_LONG_STORY_SHORT_I_NEED                                     = 10713,  -- T'make a long story short, I need ya t'find the man that had the nerve t'rob me, and get that helmet back. Not too difficult fer an adventurer like you, eh?
        AND_IF_FER_SOME_REASON_THE_MAGIC_SEAL                                = 10714,  -- And if fer some reason, the magic seal on the helmet were to be broken, we'll need ya t'...well, ya know what we'll need ya t'do then.
        BECAUSE_OF_THE_SENSITIVE_NATURE_OF_THIS_PROBLEM                      = 10715,  -- Because of the sensitive nature of this problem, not many here in Norg have been informed of what has happened. However, the men I have sent to track down the thieves should have some good information fer ya, but first ya have t'search them out.
        CURRENTLY_GILGAMESH_HAS_MEN_COMBING_VANA_DIEL_FOR                    = 10716,  -- Currently, Gilgamesh has men combing Vana'diel for clues on the whereabouts of the thieves. Search them out and learn what new information they have gathered.
        THE_SITUATION_HAS_GROWN_GRAVER_THAN_I_HAD                            = 10717,  -- The situation has grown graver than I had imagined. It is only a matter of time before the seal on the helmet breaks, if it has not already.
        TAKE_THIS_IT_CAN_BE_USED_TO_EXTINGUISH                               = 10718,  -- Take this. It can be used to extinguish the evil spirit's power for a short period of time.
        THROW_THAT_INTO_THE_MAGIC_PORTAL_AFTER_THAT                          = 10719,  -- Throw that % into the magic portal. After that, you should then be able to enter. But beware of what lurks on the other side!
        YOU_FOOL_HOW_COULD_YOU_JUST_DISPOSE_OF                               = 10720,  -- You fool! How could you just dispose of such an important item? Without it, how are you supposed to break the cursed seal on the portal!?
        BY_THE_LOOKS_OF_THIS_I_CAN_GUESS                                     = 10721,  -- By the looks of this %, I can guess that seal was already broken when you arrived at the shrine. It is amazing that the seal held for so many decades.
        YOU_HAVE_DONE_WELL_WITHOUT_YOUR_STRENGTH_AND                         = 10722,  -- You have done well, %. Without your strength and perseverance, we would not have been able to silence that evil spirit. We are all in your debt.
        HOWEVER_BEFORE_I_GIVE_YOU_YOUR_REWARD_THERE                          = 10723,  -- However, before I give you your reward, there is one more small task that I wish of you. It would be an abomination to leave the helmet in this damaged state. We must do something to repair it.
        HMMM_WE_HAVE_MOST_OF_THE_MATERIAL_REQUIRED                           = 10724,  -- Hmmm... We have most of the material required to repair it here in Norg, but I fear we may not have enough %.
        BRING_ME_ONE_I_AM_SURE_YOU_KNOW                                      = 10725,  -- Bring me one %. I am sure you know of a craftsman who can provide you with this material. I will proceed in repairing the helmet when you have brought it to me.
        THE_HELMET_IS_IN_TERRIBLE_CONDITION_HOWEVER_I                        = 10726,  -- The helmet is in terrible condition. However, I think that with %, I may be able to repair it.
        YES_THIS_IS_WHAT_I_REQUIRE_TO_REPAIR                                 = 10727,  -- Yes, this is what I require to repair the damaged helmet. I will get to work immediately. However, this may take a great deal of time. Its condition is far worse than I had imagined.
        WHY_MUST_YOU_RUSH_ME_IN_MY_WORK                                      = 10728,  -- Why must you rush me in my work!? As I told you, the helmet was in terrible condition when you brought it to me. My work must be precise if I am to return it to its former glory!
        AH_I_HAVE_JUST_FINISHED_THE_REPAIRS_TO                               = 10729,  -- Ah, %. I have just finished the repairs to the %. I had to replace a large part of the helmet, but I feel I have helped it retain its former luster.
        YES_YOUR_REWARD_I_HAVE_NOT_FORGOTTEN_LET                             = 10730,  -- Yes, your reward. I have not forgotten. Let us discuss these matters in Gilgamesh's quarters.
        ARRRG_I_M_SORRY_FER_GETTIN_YA_CAUGHT                                 = 10731,  -- Arrrg, I'm sorry fer gettin' ya caught up in our pirate affairs, but I be mighty glad t'see ya back here safe in Norrrg.
        YOU_HAVE_ME_THANKS_FER_ALL_YA_DONE                                   = 10732,  -- You have me thanks fer all ya done for us.
        IF_IT_WEREN_T_FER_YA_WE_D                                            = 10733,  -- If it weren't fer ya, we'd still be fearin' the day that demon would rear its ugly head 'n eat us all. But now that the demon's gone, that just leaves a pretty helmet t'sit on me wall.
        BUT_WHAT_GOOD_IS_A_HELMET_WITHOUT_A                                  = 10734,  -- But what good is a helmet without a head t'wear it!? This % would do you more good than it would collectin' dust in me chambers. Take it! You've earned it!
        I_AM_STILL_TAKEN_BACK_BY_HOW_MUCH                                    = 10735,  -- I am still taken back by how much you've matured much since I forged your % many moons ago. I can only imagine what great things lie before such a skilled warrior.
        SO_YOU_VE_DECIDED_TO_HELP                                            = 10736,  -- So, you've decided to help!
        SO_YOU_VE_FINALLY_DECIDED_TO_HELP                                    = 10737,  -- So, you've finally decided to help.
        CALM_DOWN_BUDDY_TRY_A_ZONE_CHANGE_1                                  = 10738,  -- Calm down buddy! Try a zone change! 1
        SAMURAI_ARTIFACT_1_FLOWCHART_1_GET_FROM_WASHU                        = 10739,  -- Samurai Artifact 1 flowchart 1: Get % from Washu.: Get % from Onzozo.
        ID_3_GIVE_THOSE_TWO_THINGS_TO_JAUCRIBAIX_4                           = 10740,  -- 3: Give those two things to Jaucribaix. 4: Do some "Sending" in the dunes (z103). 5: Bring back % and you're done!
        SAMURAI_ARTIFACT_2_FLOWCHART_1_GET_FIGHT_THE                         = 10741,  -- Samurai Artifact 2 flowchart 1: Get %.: Fight the boss in zone 144 and get %.
        ID_3_GET_TO_REPAIR_THE_4_HAND_OVER                                   = 10742,  -- 3: Get % to repair the %. 4: Hand over %, wait one day (Earth time) and you're done!
        AF_REN_WAS_SPANKED_IN_ZONE_144_BABY                                  = 10743,  -- AF: Ren was spanked in zone 144, baby.
        ARRRG_SO_YA_SAY_YA_COULDN_T_JOURNEY                                  = 10744,  -- Arrrg, so ya say ya couldn't journey deeper into the temple because a grate was blockin' yer way?
        WHAT_YA_SAW_A_STAIRWAY_ON_THE_OTHER                                  = 10745,  -- What? Ya saw a stairway on the other side of that bloomin' grate? Ha! Leave it t'the Zilart t'build somethin' crazy like that.
        BUT_THIS_AIN_T_NO_TIME_FER_COMPLAININ                                = 10746,  -- But this ain't no time fer complainin'. We've got t'figger out a way t'get t'that stairway.
        THERE_S_GOT_T_BE_SOME_WAY_T                                          = 10747,  -- There's got t'be some way t'open that wall. Some kind of key...
        ARRRG_I_VE_GOT_IT_YA_SAY_THE                                         = 10748,  -- Arrrg! I've got it! Ya say the Zilarrrt used crystals t'power their strange machines, right? Then maybe...
        I_THINK_ME_MAY_KNOW_THE_WAY_T                                        = 10749,  -- I think me may know the way t'get through that grate.
        LISTEN_UP_I_WANT_YA_T_FIND_A                                         = 10750,  -- Listen up, %. I want ya t'find a Mithra named Mary or Maroo or somethin' like that. She was in Norg a while back, but now she could be anywhere on the mainlands.
        WHY_ALL_THIS_TROUBLE_OVER_A_CAT_WELL                                 = 10751,  -- Why all this trouble over a cat? Well, when that lady was here, she tried sellin' us a strange crystal she said she found in the Sanctuary of Zi'Tah.
        I_DON_T_THINK_SHE_WAS_TRYIN_T                                        = 10752,  -- I don't think she was tryin' t'pull a fast one, but no one was interested in her booty, so she packed up and left fer somewhere else.
        BUT_NOW_THAT_ME_THINKS_OF_IT_THAT                                    = 10753,  -- But now that me thinks of it, that crystal she found in Zi'Tah may be jus' what we're lookin' fer.
        A_THIEF_LIKE_HER_WON_T_BE_EASY                                       = 10754,  -- A thief like her won't be easy t'find. I'll have me mateys around Vana'diel spread the word that yer lookin' fer a crystal like the one she has.
        IF_SHE_GETS_WIND_OF_THAT_INFO_THAT                                   = 10755,  -- If she gets wind of that info, that Maree's likely t'settle down until ya find her. We can only pray that what she has is what we need.
        ARRRG_SO_THAT_BE_THE_THAT_WE_VE                                      = 10756,  -- Arrrg, so that be the % that we've been searchin' fer. It looks like you had a hell of a time tryin' t'get yer hands on it.
        BUT_THE_REAL_HELL_IS_YET_T_COME                                      = 10757,  -- But the real hell is yet t'come, %. Crystal Warriors...floating islands... It may all seem crazy, but don't let that get in yer way. Yer Vana'diel's only hope.
        ARRRG_SO_WERE_YA_ABLE_T_MAKE_IT                                      = 10758,  -- Arrrg, so were ya able t'make it t'Tu'Lia?
        OH_SO_YA_MADE_THEM_CRYSTAL_WARRIORS_WALK                             = 10759,  -- Oh, so ya made them Crystal Warriors walk the plank now, did ya? Then that jus' leaves us with that wee prince. But first, we've got t'find a way into the darn shrine.
        IS_IT_EALD_NARRRCHE_THAT_S_KEEPIN_US                                 = 10760,  -- Is it Eald'narrrche that's keepin' us out, or is it somethin' else?
        LISTEN_CLOSE                                                         = 10761,  -- Listen close, %.
        IF_THE_PRINCE_HAD_ALREADY_OPENED_THE_GATE                            = 10762,  -- If the prince had already opened the Gate of the Gods, Vana'diel wouldn't be here anymore. But as you can see, nothin's changed so far.
        WHICH_MEANS_ALL_WE_CAN_DO_IS_WAIT                                    = 10763,  -- Which means all we can do is wait. When Eald'narche makes his move...that's when we attack!
        YOU_N_ME_BOTH_HATE_THE_ZILARRRT_MAKIN                                = 10764,  -- You'n me both hate the Zilarrrt makin' fools out of us, but there's nothing much we can do right now.
        WE_CAN_T_KNOW_WHEN_EALD_NARCHE_WILL                                  = 10765,  -- We can't know when Eald'narche will attempt t'open the gate. It could be t'morrow, fer all I know. If ya have any preparations, I'd suggest makin' 'em now.
        HEY_MISTER_LADY_YOU_LOOK_LIKE_YOU_COULD                              = 10766,  -- Hey, mister/lady]. You look like you could use some extra cash, and what easier way to get gil than by making a date with Lady Luck?
        GIVE_LUCKY_ROLL_A_TRY_LUCK_BE_A                                      = 10767,  -- Give Lucky Roll a try? Luck be a lady tonight! I'm not throwing my money away! Fill me in on the details.
        LET_ME_EXPLAIN_TO_YOU_HOW_IT_WORKS                                   = 10768,  -- Let me explain to you how it works. One game of Lucky Roll is played each Vana'diel day.
        ONE_PLAY_IS_100_GIL_BUT_AS_LONG                                      = 10769,  -- One play is 100 gil, but as long as you keep paying, you can keep playing.
        FOR_EACH_100_GIL_YOU_GET_ONE_ROLL                                    = 10770,  -- For each 100 gil, you get one roll of our six-sided die. The number that appears is added to the running total for that day.
        THE_LUCKY_ADVENTURER_WHO_ROLLS_THE_DIE_THAT                          = 10771,  -- The lucky adventurer who rolls the die that gets the running total over 400 wins...get this...a whopping 10000 gil!
        AND_THAT_S_NOT_ALL_YOU_LL_RECEIVE                                    = 10772,  -- And that's not all! You'll receive extra prizes if the total comes to 401 or 402, and a super bonus prize if your roll brings the total to exactly 400!
        BUT_BE_CAREFUL_THE_ONLY_TIME_YOU_CAN                                 = 10773,  -- But be careful; the only time you can find out the running total is after you have rolled.
        AND_THAT_S_IT_PRETTY_SIMPLE_HUH_YOU                                  = 10774,  -- And that's it! Pretty simple, huh? You can attack from the get go, or you can sit back while other people roll, and then come in for the final kill. We provide you with the die, you choose the strategy.
        ALRIGHT_ENOUGH_TALK_LET_S_GET_ROLLING                                = 10775,  -- Alright, enough talk, let's get rolling!
        YOU_ROLLED_A_THE_RUNNING_TOTAL_IS_NOW                                = 10776,  -- You rolled a...#! The running total is now #!
        CONGRATULATIONS_LADY_LUCK_HAS_SMILED_ON_YOU_TODAY                    = 10777,  -- Congratulations! Lady Luck has smiled on you today! Here's your 10000 gil!
        AND_BECAUSE_YOUR_ROLL_PUT_THE_RUNNING_TOTAL                          = 10778,  -- And because your roll put the running total at exactly 400, you receive a bonus prize!
        AND_FOR_BRINGING_THE_TOTAL_SO_CLOSE_TO                               = 10779,  -- And for bringing the total so close to 400, here is your extra prize!
        I_M_SORRY_BUT_THAT_S_IT_FOR                                          = 10780,  -- I'm sorry, but that's it for today's game of Lucky Roll. Come by tomorrow, and maybe Lady Luck will be waiting for you!
        THE_MINSTREL_OF_MELODIES_IS_MY_NAME_FOR                              = 10781,  -- The minstrel of melodies is my name, For a mere # gil I'll recall your past. Your stories of love, anger, triumph, and shame, The river of memories runs deep and vast.
        THE_MINSTREL_OF_MELODIES_IS_MY_NAME_FOR_2                            = 10782,  -- The minstrel of melodies is my name, For a mere # gil I'd recall your past. But I find that you're lacking in cash or in fame, So until that time, my kind offer will last.
        NOW_CLOSE_YOUR_EYES                                                  = 10783,  -- Now close your eyes...
        WHICH_MEMORY_WILL_YOU_HAVE_RECALLED_NOTHING_ZILART                   = 10784,  -- Which memory will you have recalled? Nothing. Zilart Missions. Norg Quests. Foreign Missions. Foreign Quests. Additional Scenarios.
