        WHAT_DO_YA_CHOOSE_LET_ME_THINK_ABOUT                                 = 11256,  -- What do ya choose? Let me think about it. %. %. %. %.
        THAT_S_WHAT_YA_WANT                                                  = 11257,  -- %. That's what ya want?
        YA_WANT_AYE_NAY                                                      = 11258,  -- Ya want %? Aye. Nay.
        ARRG_I_ALMOST_BE_FORGETTIN_ME_GIRL_WANTS                             = 11259,  -- Arrg, I almost be forgettin'. Me girl wants ya to pummel some beastie that's been hauntin' her dreams. Stuff o' nightmares, she says.
        DON_T_MAKE_MUCH_SENSE_TO_ME_BUT                                      = 11260,  -- Don't make much sense to me, but I be guessin' you know the truth of it. If ya ever need an old pirate's help, ya just let me know.
        FER_A_GIRL_WHAT_S_SAVED_THE_WORLD                                    = 11261,  -- Fer a girl what's saved the world, it be an endearin' thing fer her to be afraid of her dreams.
        BLIMEY_ARE_YA_TRYIN_T_TELL_ME_THAT                                   = 11262,  -- Blimey. Are ya tryin' t'tell me that the savior of the world can't make up his/her] mind about a simple thing like this? Guess some things never change, eh?
        BUT_WHO_BE_I_T_JUDGE_LET_ME                                          = 11263,  -- But who be I t'judge? Let me know when you've made yer decision. Jus' don't complain if all the best loot be taken!
        ARRG_SO_YOU_VE_MADE_A_DECISION                                       = 11264,  -- Arrg, so you've made a decision?
        BY_ME_BLEEDIN_EYEPATCH_I_CAN_T_BE                                    = 11265,  -- By me bleedin' eyepatch, I can't be handing over any booty when yer bag be full of flotsam and jetsam. You heroes need to learn a thing o' two about organization!
        HERE_THAT_BE_A_TREASURE_UNLIKE_ANY_YOU                               = 11266,  -- Here. That be a treasure unlike any you'll ever see again. Don't go losin' it over the side of no stinkin' ferry!
        SORRY_THE_BOSS_IS_A_LITTLE_BUSY_RIGHT                                = 11267,  -- Sorry, %, the boss is a little busy right now. Ye'll have to make yer meetin' fer another day.
        I_VE_NOT_SEEN_THE_BOSS_WITH_THAT                                     = 11268,  -- I've not seen the boss with that look on his face fer a while. I mean, we all be happy as a buccaneer in a parrot shop to have Lion back, but there's somethin' else he's not tellin' us...
        ARRG_FORGET_I_EVEN_SAID_ANYTHIN_THE_BOSS                             = 11269,  -- Arrg! Forget I even said anythin'! The boss is jus' busy, that's all. Make yer meetin' fer another day!
        WELCOME_TO_THE_MHMU_S_PORTER_SERVICE_KUPO                            = 11270,  -- Welcome to the MHMU's porter service, kupo! Which of your burdensome belongings shall I take off your hands today?
        DO_SOMETHING_KUPO_PORTER_SERVICE_BUY_A_STORAGE                       = 11271,  -- Do something, kupo? Porter service? Buy a storage slip. No, thank you.
        IS_YOUR_GOBBIEBAG_SPLITTING_AT_THE_SEAMS_MOG                         = 11272,  -- Is your gobbiebag splitting at the seams? Mog Safe spilling over? Why, an accomplished adventurer like yourself surely has more stuff than you know what to do with.
        THAT_S_WHERE_I_COME_IN_KUPO_I                                        = 11273,  -- That's where I come in, kupo. I'll gladly hold onto your prized possessions, freeing you space to gather up even grander goodies.
        TO_MAKE_USE_OF_MY_SERVICES_FIRST_YOU                                 = 11274,  -- To make use of my services, first you'll need to buy one of these storage slips for the low, low fee of # gil.
        STORAGE_SLIPS_COME_IN_NUMEROUS_VARIETIES_KUPO_EACH                   = 11275,  -- Storage slips come in numerous varieties, kupo, each corresponding to a different type of item.
        YOU_LL_WANT_TO_PERUSE_THE_FINE_PRINT                                 = 11276,  -- You'll want to peruse the fine print closely, so you don't end up paying good gil for a scrap of parchment useless for the particular item you wish to store.
        NOT_THAT_WE_MOOGLES_WOULD_OBJECT_TO_THAT                             = 11277,  -- Not that we moogles would object to that sort of donation, kupo.
        CHOOSE_THE_ITEM_YOU_WISH_TO_ENTRUST_THEN                             = 11278,  -- Choose the item you wish to entrust, then trade it to me along with a single storage slip. I will take the item and return the slip to you, marked with an invisible seal.
        INVISIBLE_TO_YOU_AT_LEAST_IT_S_PLAIN                                 = 11279,  -- Invisible to you, at least. It's plain as day to us moogles, so don't even think of trying to pull one over on us, kupo.
        WHEN_IT_COMES_TIME_TO_RETRIEVE_YOUR_ITEM                             = 11280,  -- When it comes time to retrieve your item, just trade to me a single storage slip--any slip--once again.
        I_WILL_PRESENT_YOU_WITH_A_LIST_OF                                    = 11281,  -- I will present you with a list of all the items currently in my care, and you may choose the one you wish to withdraw. Simple as that, kupo!
        WHAT_S_MORE_NO_ADDITIONAL_TRANSACTION_FEES_WILL                      = 11282,  -- What's more, no additional transaction fees will be incurred! Pretty generous of us for a change, no?
        NOW_I_BET_YOU_RE_WONDERING_WHAT_THE                                  = 11283,  -- Now I bet you're wondering what the catch is, kupo. So as not to disappoint you, there are a few!
        FOR_ONE_ANY_SIGNED_ITEMS_WILL_LOSE_THEIR                             = 11284,  -- For one, any signed items will lose their signatures if you store them with me.
        WHY_YOU_SAY_HEY_EVEN_WE_MOOGLES_AREN                                 = 11285,  -- Why, you say? Hey, even we moogles aren't perfect! It's better for both of us if you keep your most precious possessions close at hand, kupo.
        NOW_LISTEN_UP_BECAUSE_THERE_S_ANOTHER_CATCH                          = 11286,  -- Now listen up, because there's another catch, and it's a doozy.
        IF_YOU_LOSE_YOUR_STORAGE_SLIP_I_WON                                  = 11287,  -- If you lose your storage slip, I won't be able to return your item. Ever. No ifs, ands, or buts! No I'm sorry, Mister Porter Moogle, it'll never happen again! Rules are rules, kupo, and someone has to keep them.
        LAST_BUT_NOT_LEAST_I_CAN_T_ACCEPT                                    = 11288,  -- Last, but not least, I can't accept equipment bearing Magian trial insignia.
        IF_YOU_HAVE_SUCH_AN_ITEM_THAT_YOU                                    = 11289,  -- If you have such an item that you're simply dying to entrust to me, you'll have to abandon your trial first, kupo.
        AND_THAT_S_ALL_THERE_IS_TO_IT                                        = 11290,  -- And that's all there is to it. This humble moogle can hardly wait to serve you!
        BUY_SOMETHING_P_PREVIOUS_PAGE_NEXT_PAGE_CANCEL                       = 11291,  -- Buy something? (p. #/#). Previous page. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. Next page. Cancel.
        WILL_COST_YOU_GIL_DO_WE_HAVE_A                                       = 11292,  -- % will cost you # gil. Do we have a deal, kupo?
        DEAL_KUPO_CURRENT_GIL_CHECK_STORABLE_ITEMS_DEAL                      = 11293,  -- Deal, kupo? (Current gil: #). Check storable items. Deal. No deal.
        THE_WILL_ALLOW_YOU_TO_STORE_THE_FOLLOWING                            = 11294,  -- The % will allow you to store the following items:
        ID_11295                                                             = 11295,  -- %.
        ID_11296                                                             = 11296,  -- %.
        AND_THAT_S_ALL                                                       = 11297,  -- ...and that's all.
        P_PREVIOUS_PAGE_NEXT_PAGE_CANCEL                                     = 11298,  -- % (p. #/#). Previous page. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. Next page. Cancel.
        WARNING_IF_YOU_LOSE_YOUR_WHILE_STORING_A                             = 11299,  -- Warning! If you lose your % while storing a corresponding item, you will be forever unable to retrieve that item!
        IS_THAT_I_SEE_KUPO                                                   = 11300,  -- Is that % I see, kupo?
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_RETRIEVE_AN_ITEM_CONFIRM                            = 11301,  -- What will you do? Retrieve an item. Confirm storable items. Nothing.
        RETRIEVE_AN_ITEM_P_PREVIOUS_PAGE_NEXT_PAGE                           = 11302,  -- Retrieve an item? (p. #/#). Previous page. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. Next page. Cancel.
        RETRIEVE_RETRIEVE_IT_LEAVE_IT                                        = 11303,  -- Retrieve %? Retrieve it. Leave it.
        YOU_RETRIEVE_FROM_THE_PORTER_MOOGLE_S_CARE                           = 11304,  -- You retrieve % from the porter moogle's care.
        KUPO_I_M_ALREADY_TAKING_CARE_OF_THAT                                 = 11305,  -- Kupo? I'm already taking care of that item for you.
        YES_VERY_WELL_YOUR_PRECIOUS_PROPERTY_IS_SAFE                         = 11306,  -- %, yes? Very well! Your precious property is safe with me, kupo!
        OF_ITEM_IS_IT_VERY_WELL_YOUR_PRECIOUS                                = 11307,  -- # [variety/varieties] of item, is it? Very well! Your precious property is safe with me, kupo!
        IS_THAT_A_MAGIAN_INSIGNIA_I_SEE_ON                                   = 11308,  -- Is that a Magian insignia I see on that %? You'll have to abandon your trial before I can take it off your hands, kupo.
        THAT_APPEARS_TO_BE_AUGMENTED_I_M_SORRY                               = 11309,  -- That % appears to be augmented. I'm sorry, but I can't accept such specialized gear, kupo.
        CURIOUS_AS_TO_WHETHER_I_CAN_ACCEPT_THAT                              = 11310,  -- Curious as to whether I can accept that item? Let me check my annals.
        WHY_YES_I_CAN_CAN_BE_STORED_WITH                                     = 11311,  -- Why, yes I can! % can be stored with %.
        WHY_IT_LOOKS_AS_IF_YOU_HAVE_LOCATED                                  = 11312,  -- Why, it looks as if you have % located in your [inventory/Mog Safe/Mog Safe 2/Mog House storage/Mog Locker/Mog Satchel/Mog Sack/Mog Case/Mog Wardrobe/Mog Wardrobe 2/Mog Wardrobe 3/Mog Wardrobe 4/Mog Wardrobe 5/Mog Wardrobe 6/Mog Wardrobe 7/Mog Wardrobe 8/Recycle Bin]!
        STORABLE_ITEM                                                        = 11313,  -- Storable item: % (#)
        STORABLE_ITEM_2                                                      = 11314,  -- Storable item: % (#)
        ID_0_1_2_3_2                                                         = 11315,  -- 0: # 1: # 2: # 3: #
        ID_4_5_6_7_2                                                         = 11316,  -- 4: # 5: # 6: # 7: #
        NO_ID                                                                = 11317,  -- no: # id: #
        NO_ID_RES                                                            = 11318,  -- no: # id: # res: #
        TB                                                                   = 11319,  -- TB: #
        NPC_INDEX_OUT_OF_RANGE                                               = 11320,  -- NPC index out of range.
        ERROR_CODE                                                           = 11321,  -- ERROR CODE: # / #
        YA_LOOK_MORE_LIKE_PUGIL_BAIT_THAN_AN                                 = 11322,  -- Ya look more like pugil bait than an adventurer to me. Begone! I've bigger fish to reel in.
        HMPH_SO_YA_FANCY_YOURSELF_A_HERO_HEROINE                             = 11323,  -- Hmph, so ya fancy yourself a hero/heroine], eh? I guess ya look the part enough. How about I let ya in on a little secret?
        YOU_VE_HEARD_OF_THE_VOIDWATCH_OPERATION_HAVEN                        = 11324,  -- You've heard of the Voidwatch operation, haven't ya? Well, I'm in charge of dolin' out missions for it in these parts.
        THE_OFFICIAL_LINE_IS_THAT_THE_GRAND_DUCHY                            = 11325,  -- The official line is that the Grand Duchy of Jeuno oversees the whole organization, with local branches in each of the three nations. But any sailor worth 'is salt should already know that; elsewise, I'd suggest pullin' the kelp outcha ears an' payin' attention!
        ANYWAY_PROTECTING_MULTIPLE_NATIONS_IS_DIFFICULT_YER_CEASELESSLY      = 11326,  -- Anyway, protecting multiple nations is difficult. Yer ceaselessly runnin' long n' lonely border patrols lest a sudden squall blow yer hard-won peace clean to flinders. But you know what's easier to control than borders? Information. The extent of it that gets released to the public amounts to nothin' more than the mud-caked tip of Zuug the Shoreleaper's massive spear.
        THE_MORE_DEFTLY_YA_HIDE_THAT_UNPLEASANT_INTELLIGENCE                 = 11327,  -- The more deftly ya hide that unpleasant intelligence, the safer the citizens will feel. However, even a tiny point of truth can rip a nation to shreds if it pokes through. That's why ya have to keep things under wraps, ya see.
        JUST_LIKE_THE_OLD_ADAGE_ASSERTS_IGNORANCE_TRULY                      = 11328,  -- Just like the old adage asserts, ignorance truly is bliss. Bweheheheh.
        AND_SO_THIS_IS_WHERE_WE_COME_IN                                      = 11329,  -- And so, this is where we come in. We handle problems th' Duchy an' other nations don't want to dirty their pretty lil' white-gloved hands wid. Think of us as very unofficial--and very well-paid--deck swabbers, bwehehehe.
        COURSE_THIS_MEANS_BEIN_AS_BLACK_EARTED_AN                            = 11330,  -- Course this means bein' as black-'earted an' cold as th' void from which these abominations strike. And since so few know of our existence, we can go about our business in our own fashion. We need not concern ourselves with the political quagmire people call diplomacy.
        THE_LONG_AND_THE_SHORT_OF_IT_IS                                      = 11331,  -- The long and the short of it is this: we're a necessary evil.
        COME_TO_THINK_OF_IT_YOU_ADVENTURERS_AREN                             = 11332,  -- Come to think of it, you adventurers aren't so different from us. As long as ya can reap a reward, you'll do as needs doin' widdout so much as a roll of the eyes; and that's exactly the kind of attitude we need.
        SO_WHADDYA_SAY_WANT_TO_EARN_A_LITTLE                                 = 11333,  -- So, whaddya say? Want to earn a little coin by slinkin' through the shadows?
        ENLIST_IN_THE_OPERATION_YES_I_M_INTRIGUED                            = 11334,  -- Enlist in the operation? Yes, I'm intrigued. No, it's too shady.
        FINE_GO_BACK_T_HIDIN_BEHIND_YER_MUM                                  = 11335,  -- Fine, go back t' hidin' behind yer mum's skirts if yer so scared of the dark. But don't go flappin' those oversized lips of yers about us to anyone, lest ya wake one morning wid none at all. But if ya ever get more heart than a rabbit, talk to me again and maybe maybe we'll find a use for ya.
        COME_CRAWLIN_BACK_HAVE_YA                                            = 11336,  -- Come crawlin' back, have ya?
        A_LAUDABLE_DECISION_NOW_PAY_ATTENTION_CAUSE_I                        = 11337,  -- A laudable decision. Now, pay attention, 'cause I'm not goin' to repeat myself.
        WE_HAVE_OPERATIVES_STATIONED_IN_BOTH_KAZHAM_AND                      = 11338,  -- We have operatives stationed in both Kazham and Rabao--scratch their backs, and they'll scratch yers.
        WHAT_S_THIS_SCARED_ALREADY_I_CAN_T                                   = 11339,  -- What's this, scared already? I can't hear myself think o'er the sound of yer knees knockin', so pull y'self together till I've had my say. I never said this had to be a solo mission, whelp.
        OTHER_ADVENTURERS_HAVE_ENLISTED_WITH_US_MOST_OF                      = 11340,  -- Other adventurers have enlisted with us, most of them so strong they could eviscerate the likes of ya with a fingernail. Any one of them should make a fine companion. As much as I would love to prove my strength to ya on the battlefield, us officers are tasked only with supplyin' the locations and names of yer targets. So there. Oh, and ya better show some initiative from start to finish, or ya won't be gettin' anythin' from the pyxides.
        I_HEAR_THE_REWARDS_FOR_COMPLETIN_THESE_TASKS                         = 11341,  -- I hear the rewards for completin' these tasks are quite the treasures, too. Should ya happen to chance upon some courage within that craven heart of yours, ya may also fight alone and save them all for y'self.
        UGH_I_VE_HAD_ENOUGH_OF_THAT_REPULSIVE                                = 11342,  -- Ugh, I've had enough of that repulsive mug of yers. Get out of my face and come back when ya've actually done somethin'.
        HALT_BELAY_THAT_ORDER_I_MAY_NOT_LIKE                                 = 11343,  -- Halt! Belay that order! I may not like the look of ya, but you'll be needin' this nonetheless.
        EVEN_A_DIM_GREENHORN_LIKE_Y_SELF_KNOWS                               = 11344,  -- Even a dim greenhorn like y'self knows what % looks like, right?
        JUST_SHOW_THIS_TO_MY_FELLOW_AGENTS_IN                                = 11345,  -- Just show this to my fellow agents in Kazham and Rabao.
        I_M_SURE_I_DON_T_NEED_TO                                             = 11346,  -- I'm sure I don't need to tell someone of yer oh-so-legendary stature that it's used to call forth Voidwalkers. However, procurin' some % might give ya the upper hand...not that yer haughty highness would need it.
        ALSO_MY_DIRECTIVES_INVOLVE_ONLY_THE_CLOAK_AND                        = 11347,  -- Also, my directives involve only the cloak-and-dagger aspects of this trade. I find no reason to concern myself with the mundane particulars of our operations. Should ya wish to risk having yer ears jabbered off over such banalities, go see a Voidwatch Officer.
        AH_THERE_YA_ARE_I_HEARD_ABOUT_YER                                    = 11348,  -- Ah, there ya are. I heard about yer exploits in Kazham and Rabao. Maybe I misjudged you...
        BUT_DON_T_ASSUME_YA_VE_EARNED_OUR                                    = 11349,  -- But don't assume ya've earned our trust after two measly missions. Come back when yer a bit more seasoned, then I might have something for ya.
        WHY_DO_I_THINK_THIS_JOB_WOULD_SEND                                   = 11350,  -- Why do I think this job would send you crying back to yer mother? Because the boss said so...in not quite so many words.
        THINK_YER_A_BETTER_JUDGE_OF_YER_OWN                                  = 11351,  -- Think yer a better judge of yer own abilities than the boss, eh?
        THEN_TRY_FINDING_A_BETTER_WAY_TO_GRAB                                = 11352,  -- Then try finding a better way to grab the boss's attention.
        HOW_EXACTLY_DO_YA_ACCOMPLISH_THAT_HAHAHA_DON                         = 11353,  -- How exactly do ya accomplish that? Hahaha, don't make me split my sides. I thought ya called yourself an adventurer. Then use that half-rotten melon ya call a head and think of something y'self.
        IN_OUR_WORLD_PERSEVERANCE_IS_INDISPENSABLE_NO_MATTER                 = 11354,  -- In our world, perseverance is indispensable. No matter how much vitriol I spew, ya keep cryin' to me fer more. I can fault yer ugly mug, but not yer determination.
        IF_YA_WANT_MY_BOSS_TO_RECOGNIZE_YER                                  = 11355,  -- If ya want my boss to recognize yer skills, try to do something worthy of an adventurer. It may take a while for a whelp like ya, but my boss isn't blind. He'll take notice of ya eventually.
        AS_FOR_HOW_TO_MAKE_HIM_TAKE_NOTICE                                   = 11356,  -- As for how to make him take notice, that half-rotten melon of yours should be able to figure it out. Best of luck to ya. Looks like you'll need it.
        AH_THERE_YA_ARE_I_HEARD_ABOUT_YA                                     = 11357,  -- Ah, there ya are. I heard about ya exploits in Kazham and Rabao, and...well, I suppose I misjudged ya.
        I_HAVE_IN_MY_POSSESSION_A_DOCUMENT_REQUESTING                        = 11358,  -- I have in my possession a document requesting yer presence, signed by none other than the head man himself. If he recognizes yer talents, who am I to question them.
        ANYWAY_LET_S_BRIEF_YA_ON_YER_NEXT                                    = 11359,  -- Anyway, let's brief ya on yer next assignment, shall we?
        HAVE_YA_HEARD_THE_STORY_OF_THE_AIRBORNE                              = 11360,  -- Have ya heard the story of the airborne palace? That's where you'll be going.
        HOW_IN_A_MOBLIN_MINESHAFT_SHOULD_I_KNOW                              = 11361,  -- How in a Moblin mineshaft should I know? As far as I'm concerned, it's nothing but a wet nurse's tale!
        I_VE_HEARD_MANY_ACCOUNTS_FROM_THE_NEAR                               = 11362,  -- I've heard many accounts from the Near East of castles that float upon the sea, but one that flies in the sky? That's madness!
        THE_BOSS_THOUGH_HE_SHOULD_HAVE_SOME_ANSWERS                          = 11363,  -- The boss though, he should have some answers for ya. He's waitin' in his chambers, so go on in and stop shootin' the sheep with me.
        AHOY_TIS_GOOD_TO_SEE_YER_HALE_N                                      = 11364,  -- Ahoy, %! 'Tis good to see yer hale 'n hearty, matey.
        I_DIDN_T_WANT_T_BURDEN_YE_WIT                                        = 11365,  -- I didn't want t' burden ye wit' another one of me infamous ramblings, but what kind of captain would I be if I sent me crew to sea wit' nary a jib nor oar? Just bite the bollard fer a bit and I'll be done as quick as possible...but I can't promise nothin', fer when ye've spent as much time twixt mast n' main as me, time starts t' mean somethin' else entirely.
        YE_LL_NEXT_BE_SHOVIN_OFF_FER_SKY                                     = 11366,  -- Ye'll next be shovin' off fer Sky. Aye, that's right. Tu'Lia be yer destination.
        THIS_AIN_T_NO_BIBIKI_BAY_OR_BUBURIMU                                 = 11367,  -- This ain't no Bibiki Bay or Buburimu Peninsula--hardly a soul knows 'bout this ethereal archipelago. To make matters worse, ev'ryone in ports across Vana'diel be gettin' their timbers shivered over some unseen scourge. And I'd be willin' t' wager ye all the gil in Norg that Jeuno knows somethin' 'bout this we don't.
        BURST_ME_BARNACLES_IF_I_DIDN_T_KNOW                                  = 11368,  -- Burst me barnacles! If I didn't know better, I'd swear this was nothin' more'n the ramblings of some blunder'n boatswain. Arrrg, gone are the days when we pirates were the worst of the world's ills, matey.
        STILL_WE_SEEM_T_BOTH_BE_STEERIN_OURRR                                = 11369,  -- Still, we seem t' both be steerin' ourrr ships t'wards the same X on the proverbial treasure map fer the time bein'... Yet seein' how our plans be wide as the horiz'n, we best not turn a patched eye to these problems.
        KEEP_THIS_INFERMATION_BELOW_DECK_IF_YE_CATCH                         = 11370,  -- Keep this infermation below deck, if ye catch me drift. The situation be bad enough without the entire continent up in arms. In any case, I'll make sure t' apprrrise ye of any new developments if I get wind of 'em. Ye can count on that--cross me own plank and hope t' fly, stick a pegleg on me thigh.
        I_FERGOT_TO_MENTION_SOMETHIN_YER_STILL_HOARDIN                       = 11371,  -- I fergot to mention somethin'! Yer still hoardin' that %, ain'tcha? I think it's s'pposed to hatch or whatnot if'n ye raise it right. I ain't too sure on the partic'lars, though. Best ye check wit' me first mate Kieran on that.
        HE_KNOWS_THE_REST_OF_THE_AFT_FLOTATION                               = 11372,  -- He knows the rest of the aft flotation--arrrg, I mean apt infermation. Maybe I truly do have a family of crows roostin' in me ol' crow's nest. May that stone serve ye well in yer travels, though, as ye may very well be the realm's only hope.
        LASTLY_DON_T_DO_ANYTHING_OUT_THERE_A                                 = 11373,  -- Lastly, don't do anything out there a salty sea dog like meself wouldn't do, matey.
        OH_YOU_RE_BACK_THE_BOSS_IS_WAITIN                                    = 11374,  -- Oh, you're back. The boss is waitin'. Hurry inside before ya make both me and him angry.
        FIRST_THANK_YE_FER_DOIN_WHAT_NEEDS_BE                                = 11375,  -- First, thank ye fer doin' what needs be done. Me heart, it be waterlogged with guilt fer always makin' ye perform these underwater operations.
        YET_YE_BE_THE_ONLY_ONE_I_CAN                                         = 11376,  -- Yet ye be the only one I can trust. Wit' all these lily-livered deckhands in me service--none be fit to hold a sword, if ye ask me.
        WHICH_MAKES_IT_ALL_THE_WORSE_T_TELL                                  = 11377,  -- ...Which makes it all the worse t' tell ye that we be gettin' drenched in this Voidwalker squall, and we be takin' on water faster'n we can bail it out. We still don't know much 'bout this perfect storm o' sorts either, which I find queerer than a cryin' kraken.
        THE_WESTERLY_WINDS_BRING_WIT_EM_TALES_OF                             = 11378,  -- The westerly winds bring wit' 'em tales of destruction from the Near East as well.
        SADLY_ME_HANDS_BE_TIED_AND_I_HAVEN                                   = 11379,  -- Sadly, me hands be tied and I haven't the time t' drop down no dinghies fer ourrr neighbors to the east.
        WHICH_IS_WHY_I_BE_SENDIN_YE_I                                        = 11380,  -- Which is why I be sendin' ye. I figured ye'd be hoistin' sail and shovin' off soon as ye heard this anyway, and that fire in yer belly be what we need most right now.
        THE_VIOLENCE_BE_SPREADIN_LIKE_SELBINA_BUTTER_ON                      = 11381,  -- The violence be spreadin' like Selbina butter on bread, and no matter how many fiends ye slay, thar be no end t' 'em. We ain't got the foggiest idea what be goin' on.
        YE_BE_THE_BALLAST_THAT_KEEPS_VANA_DIEL                               = 11382,  -- Ye be the ballast that keeps Vana'diel upright, %, and the realm needs ye now mor'n ever. This may not be worth a grain of salt, comin' from an old sailor tucked safely away in his captain's quarters, but don't go overboard wit' the heroics.
        WELL_WELL_IT_SEEMS_YOU_HAVE_QUITE_A                                  = 11383,  -- Well, well...it seems you have quite a diverse circle of acquaintances. Know many individuals. It's remarkable that you've managed to make connections with a pirate, of all professions.
        ALL_THE_MORE_IMPRESSIVE_IS_THAT_HUMANS_COULD                         = 11384,  -- All the more impressive is that humans could place such a monumental object into the sky. How regrettable that such technology was lost to the ages. Eluded the annals.
        IN_ANY_CASE_THE_CORSAIR_IS_CORRECT_IN                                = 11385,  -- In any case, the corsair is correct in asserting that the intruders' influence is spreading. Extending its tendrils.
        YOUR_VALIANT_EFFORTS_HAVE_SO_FAR_MITIGATED_THE                       = 11386,  -- Your valiant efforts have so far mitigated the destruction, but soon you must face the scourge within Walk of Echoes. An inevitable encounter.
        IN_WHAT_FORM_IS_THIS_SCOURGE_MANIFEST_YOU                            = 11387,  -- In what form is this scourge manifest, you wonder? Ponder its identity?
        YOU_HAVE_TRAVERSED_THE_REALM_INNUMERABLE_TIMES_AND                   = 11388,  -- You have traversed the realm innumerable times and confronted myriad entities. A plethora of personages. Then perhaps then you can intuit my answer. Kupofried has offered to help expose the true nature of this threat, but such efforts have so far proven fruitless.
        IT_HAS_US_ALL_DROWNING_IN_A_RIVER                                    = 11389,  -- It has us all drowning in a river of ignorance. Clawing clumsily at a mist of misunderstandings.
        WHEN_THE_RIVER_HAS_RUN_DRY_I_SHALL                                   = 11390,  -- When the river has run dry, I shall apprise you of any findings immediately. That silver-tongued sailor uttered a similar comment, but it bears repeating. Its iteration is warranted. Your prowess has never possessed such import as it soon will.
        WHILE_THE_VOIDWALKERS_MAY_BE_A_CONCERN_HAVEN                         = 11391,  -- While the Voidwalkers may be a concern, haven't you other endeavors to undertake? Horizons to expand?
        THE_BONDS_YOU_FORM_WITH_THE_DENIZENS_OF                              = 11392,  -- The bonds you form with the denizens of Vana'diel may be not be visible, but they are pertinent. Their significance is palpable.
        WHEN_THE_TIME_COMES_THESE_BONDS_WILL_CONSTITUTE                      = 11393,  -- When the time comes, these bonds will constitute the source of your strength. A fountain of fortitude.
        AND_ON_THAT_NOTE_WE_MUST_PART_SCATTER                                = 11394,  -- And on that note, we must part. Scatter to the winds. May we meet again, %.
        YOU_AGAIN_I_STILL_CAN_T_CONCEIVE_OF                                  = 11395,  -- You again? I still can't conceive of what an airborne palace would look like, but it sounds as if the boss's briefing was sufficient for ya to get an idea.
        I_SUPPOSE_I_LL_LEAVE_THE_TRAVELING_TO                                = 11396,  -- I suppose I'll leave the traveling to fantastical and incomprehensible locales to you. Anyway, I suggest ya get yer priorities straight while ya can.
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_DO_NOTHING_FOR_NOW_ASK                                 = 11397,  -- What will you do? Nothing for now. Ask a bunch of questions. Participate in Voidwatch Ops. Request debriefing. Request % Check voidstone stock. Request reward issuance.
        LIKE_I_SAID_I_M_ONLY_HERE_TO                                         = 11398,  -- Like I said, I'm only here to tell ya where and what. I'll leave the cloud-skippin' mumbo jumbo to you.
        IF_YA_TRULY_NEED_TO_KNOW_SOMETHING_SEEK                              = 11399,  -- If ya truly need to know something, seek out a whatchamacallit...a Voidwatch Officer. Yes, that's who ya should ask. Didn't I tell ya that already?! Remember, it's not my job to deal with petty details.
        VERY_WELL_THEN_LET_S_GET_YA_READY                                    = 11400,  -- Very well then, let's get ya ready to ship out to that airborne palace immediately.
        WHAT_YA_TRULY_THOUGHT_YA_COULD_JUST_GO                               = 11401,  -- What? Ya truly thought ya could just go prancin' up there without fulfilling yer duties?! I don't know where ya come from, but here in Norg, we have to work to get what we want! First, we need yer services in the Li'Telor region. Ya can spread yer little wings and take to the sky after that's done.
        NOW_WHERE_TO_DISPATCH_YA_HOW_ABOUT_THE                               = 11402,  -- Now, where to dispatch ya... How about the Sanctuary of Zi'Tah, the Boyahda Tree and...last but not least, Ro'Maeve? Those three jurisdictions should do nicely.
        NO_NEED_TO_MAKE_WATER_IN_YER_BRITCHES                                = 11403,  -- No need to make water in yer britches about their order, either. Simply completin' yer objectives in the appointed sectors is enough for me. Oh yes, and be sure to report back to me when you're finished. Unfortunately fer ya, I haven't the power to read people's thoughts.
        IS_THAT_A_SCOWL_OF_INSUBORDINATION_ON_YER                            = 11404,  -- Is that a scowl of insubordination on yer face? Hah! I spit in yer general direction! Ya adventurers are supposed to enjoy adventuring, no? Otherwise, why would ya be dubbed adventurers? Now go out there and make the Voidwatch proud!
        ADMITTEDLY_I_M_SOMEWHAT_HESITANT_TO_GRANT_YA                         = 11405,  -- Admittedly, I'm somewhat hesitant to grant ya this privilege, but I suppose you've earned it. Yes, I'm saying ya may finally embark for that airborne continent. Hmmm...are these names code or somethin'? I've never heard any of them before! Maybe you have, though.
        I_M_IN_THE_DARK_ABOUT_ALL_THIS                                       = 11406,  -- I'm in the dark about all this, but the captain assured me that yer % has accrued enough energy. Apparently you'll be needin' it in the near future.
        MOVIN_ON_YOU_LL_BE_DISPATCHED_TO_THE                                 = 11407,  -- Movin' on, you'll be dispatched to the followin' three areas.
        THE_RU_AUN_GARDENS_VE_LUGANNON_PALACE_AND                            = 11408,  -- The Ru'Aun Gardens, Ve'Lugannon Palace, and the Shrine of Ru'Avitau. Ugh, I'm tyin' my tongue in knots just trying to say all that.
        YA_REMEMBER_THEM_YET_GOOD_GET_GOIN_THEN                              = 11409,  -- Ya remember them yet? Good. Get goin', then. As always, report back to me when yer finished fricasseein' yer foes.
        AND_BRING_ME_BACK_A_SOUVENIR_WILL_YA                                 = 11410,  -- And bring me back a souvenir, will ya?
        ARE_YA_ABSOLUTELY_SURE_YA_GOT_ALL_THAT                               = 11411,  -- Are ya absolutely sure ya got all that? Fine, then get on gettin' on.
        YOU_VE_STILL_GOTTA_GO_TO_NOW_LEAVE                                   = 11412,  -- You've still gotta go to [the Sanctuary of Zi'Tah/the Boyahda Tree/the Sanctuary of Zi'Tah./the Boyahda Tree./Ro'Maeve.][, the Boyahda Tree,/ and Ro'Maeve./ and the Boyahda Tree.][ and Ro'Maeve./] Now leave me be.
        YOU_VE_STILL_GOTTA_GO_TO_NOW_LEAVE_2                                 = 11413,  -- You've still gotta go to [the Ru'Aun Gardens/Ve'Lugannon Palace/the Ru'Aun Gardens./Ve'Lugannon Palace./the Shrine of Ru'Avitau.][, Ve'Lugannon Palace,/ and the Shrine of Ru'Avitau./ and Ve'Lugannon Palace.][ and the Shrine of Ru'Avitau./] Now leave me be.
        THE_RU_AUN_GARDENS_VE_LUGANNON_PALACE_AND_2                          = 11414,  -- The Ru'Aun Gardens, Ve'Lugannon Palace, and the Shrine of Ru'Avitau. How many times do ya have to ask!?
        HOW_MANY_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_NONE_JUST_ONE                                = 11415,  -- How many would you like? None. Just one. Fill me up!
        HERE_IS_WHAT_YOU_REQUESTED                                           = 11416,  -- Here is what you requested.
        IT_SEEMS_YOU_ALREADY_POSSESS_STONES_WHICH_IS                         = 11417,  -- It seems you already possess # stones, which is the maximum allocation. I believe you have a sufficient supply for the time being.
        I_REGRET_TO_INFORM_YOU_THAT_OUR_STOCK                                = 11418,  -- I regret to inform you that our stock has been depleted. The next shipment is expected to arrive in # [minute/minutes] (Earth time).
